CRM Project - Customer Analysis

📌 Project Overview

This project aims to analyze customer data within a CRM system to extract meaningful insights and enhance business strategies. The analysis includes customer segmentation, retention analysis, and predictive modeling.

📂 Dataset

The dataset consists of customer information, transaction history, and behavioral metrics. It includes fields such as:

Customer ID: Unique identifier for each customer.

Purchase History: Record of transactions.

Engagement Metrics: Interaction data with the business.

Demographic Information: Age, location, etc.

🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used

Python: Primary programming language

Pandas & NumPy: Data manipulation and analysis

Matplotlib & Seaborn: Data visualization

Scikit-learn: Machine learning models

SQL: Querying and data extraction

🔍 Key Analyses Performed

1. Data Preprocessing

Handled missing values

Removed duplicates

Standardized data formats

2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Distribution of customer demographics

Trends in purchasing behavior

Correlation between engagement and retention

3. Customer Segmentation

Used clustering techniques (e.g., K-Means)

Identified high-value customers

Defined targeted marketing strategies

4. Churn Prediction

Applied classification models (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, etc.)

Evaluated model performance using accuracy and precision metrics

Identified key factors influencing churn

📊 Results & Insights

Key customer segments were identified for targeted marketing.

Retention strategies were proposed based on churn analysis.

Predictive models provided actionable insights for customer management.

🚀 Future Improvements

Implement deep learning for better churn prediction.

Enhance feature engineering for improved model accuracy.

Integrate real-time analytics for dynamic decision-making.

📝 How to Run the Project

Install required libraries: pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the Jupyter Notebook: jupyter notebook CRM_Project.ipynb

Follow the notebook cells step by step for analysis.



